WEBVTT

00:07.500 --> 00:10.208
(FILM CREW CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY)

00:10.291 --> 00:12.500
-CREW 1: Press play here.
-Okay.

00:12.583 --> 00:14.583
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:14.666 --> 00:16.250
And that's the same songs
that we had?

00:16.333 --> 00:17.708
-CREW 1: It is, yeah...
-Okay.

00:17.791 --> 00:21.291
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:21.375 --> 00:23.416
(PAPER RUSTLING)

00:23.500 --> 00:24.958
OSCAR ISAAC: Hey,
can I talk to you for a second?

00:25.041 --> 00:26.375
HAGAI LEVI: Yeah, sure.
What's going on?

00:26.458 --> 00:28.875
-OSCAR: I was looking
at the original.
-HAGAI: Mm-hmm.

00:28.958 --> 00:30.500
-In two, right?
-HAGAI: Yeah.

00:30.583 --> 00:33.291
-OSCAR: And Marianne
in that one...
-HAGAI: Yeah.

00:33.375 --> 00:36.875
She does have kind of
a different energy
at the beginning of the...

00:36.958 --> 00:40.208
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:40.291 --> 00:43.666
OSCAR: There's this great moment
where she goes into
the refrigerator and--

00:43.750 --> 00:46.541
Like the equivalent
or something,
like a version of...

00:46.625 --> 00:50.125
CREW 2: Right, here we go.
And go ahead.

00:50.208 --> 00:54.375
-CREW 3: Do you
want the door open?
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:55.583 --> 00:58.291
(BELL RINGING)

00:58.375 --> 01:00.291
CREW 4: All right.
Stand by to roll, guys.

01:00.375 --> 01:03.416
-Let's get slate in. Okay.
-CREW 5: Ten seconds...

01:05.500 --> 01:06.583
CREW 6: Marker.

01:07.583 --> 01:09.916
DIRECTOR: And action.

01:10.000 --> 01:15.500
-(RAIN PATTERING)
-♪ (MUSIC PLAYING ON EARBUDS) ♪

01:28.916 --> 01:29.958
AVA LEVY: Daddy!

01:31.416 --> 01:34.833
-Why can't I just call Mommy?
-(RAIN PATTERING)

01:36.416 --> 01:38.791
JONATHAN LEVY: (GROANS)
Because, sweetie,

01:38.875 --> 01:42.000
you already said good night
to Mommy.

01:42.083 --> 01:44.375
You talked to her already,
remember?

01:44.458 --> 01:45.750
But I forgot to show her

01:45.833 --> 01:47.833
the picture I drew
in the kitchen.

01:47.916 --> 01:49.750
Yeah, well...

01:49.833 --> 01:51.625
she'll be here tomorrow
when you get home from school,

01:51.708 --> 01:53.250
and you can show her then, okay?

01:53.333 --> 01:56.250
-(RAIN PATTERING)
-(BIRD CHIRPING)

01:56.333 --> 01:58.666
How do you know
she's gonna be here?

01:59.791 --> 02:01.083
How do I know?

02:01.166 --> 02:03.791
Because she is coming at noon.

02:03.875 --> 02:06.166
Her train gets in
at twelve o'clock.

02:07.291 --> 02:08.458
Close your eyes, kiddo.

02:18.125 --> 02:20.000
(RUSTLING)

02:32.541 --> 02:33.583
(EXHALES)

03:07.166 --> 03:13.000
♪ (PIANO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:18.166 --> 03:22.000
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

03:25.125 --> 03:30.125
(HUMMING)

03:45.125 --> 03:48.375
(SIGHS)

04:12.416 --> 04:13.916
(DOOR OPENS)

04:16.416 --> 04:17.666
(DOOR CLOSES)

04:18.416 --> 04:21.666
(RATTLING)

04:33.125 --> 04:36.041
-Hi. You're awake.
-Yeah, you know.

04:36.125 --> 04:37.750
So, you made it out of there?

04:37.833 --> 04:39.500
-Ah, yeah!
-JONATHAN: That's great!

04:39.583 --> 04:41.041
I ended up taking
the nine o'clock.

04:41.125 --> 04:42.208
JONATHAN: Fantastic!

04:43.333 --> 04:44.625
Ava's gonna be thrilled.

04:44.708 --> 04:47.000
I told her she wouldn't see you
until after school tomorrow.

04:47.083 --> 04:48.166
Oh, yeah.
How's she been sleeping?

04:48.250 --> 04:50.916
You'll do pick-up
in the morning? Yeah?

04:51.000 --> 04:54.250
Uh, she's sleeping great.
That rain app you got is genius.

04:54.333 --> 04:56.458
-MIRA LEVY: Good.
-She doesn't wake up anymore.

04:56.541 --> 04:57.625
MIRA: That's great.

04:57.708 --> 04:59.583
JONATHAN: So, how was the train?
Did you sleep?

04:59.666 --> 05:01.666
MIRA: Uh... yeah.

05:01.750 --> 05:04.583
Um, not really,
I-- I did some work, I read.

05:04.666 --> 05:06.208
-It's...
-Good.

05:10.416 --> 05:12.708
You just ditched the dinner
last minute?

05:12.791 --> 05:14.541
Yeah. I told Ackerman
Ava was sick.

05:14.625 --> 05:16.041
He was bummed,
but he really couldn't do

05:16.125 --> 05:17.458
-anything about it.
-(JONATHAN CHUCKLES)

05:17.541 --> 05:19.291
-Don't use that one too often.
-MIRA: Hmm.

05:20.916 --> 05:21.875
(MIRA EXHALES)

05:21.958 --> 05:23.166
So, you didn't eat.
You must be hungry.

05:23.250 --> 05:24.500
You want a little something
to eat?

05:24.583 --> 05:26.375
-MIRA: No, I'm not hungry.
-There's some pasta left over

05:26.458 --> 05:27.500
from Ava's dinner.

05:27.583 --> 05:29.000
It's not gonna win any awards,

05:29.083 --> 05:30.250
-but, uh--
-MIRA: No, thanks.

05:30.333 --> 05:31.416
JONATHAN: Okay.

05:32.916 --> 05:35.625
Do we have a bottle of wine
open, by chance?

05:35.708 --> 05:37.500
JONATHAN:
I don't know, let's see.

05:38.541 --> 05:39.541
Yes.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.208
MIRA: Thanks.

05:43.500 --> 05:44.833
(PHONE CHIMES)

05:50.000 --> 05:51.083
It's, uh...

05:52.166 --> 05:54.916
Kate. She thinks I'm in-- Oh!

05:55.000 --> 05:57.083
-West Coast for some reason.
-JONATHAN: Right.

05:58.125 --> 05:59.833
How are she and Peter?

05:59.916 --> 06:01.916
They doing okay?
Everything all right over there?

06:02.000 --> 06:04.583
MIRA: Yeah, I think so.
Usual drama, nothing new.

06:04.666 --> 06:06.166
-Why?
-(WINE POURING)

06:06.250 --> 06:09.500
No, 'cause I tried to get, uh,
lunch with Peter the other day.

06:09.583 --> 06:13.375
I had some free time, and just,
I feel like he's avoiding me.

06:13.458 --> 06:15.583
He's just been blowing me off
the last couple months.

06:16.291 --> 06:17.625
Did you ask him why?

06:17.708 --> 06:19.083
I tried to.
He just mumbled something

06:19.166 --> 06:20.625
about it being a busy time.

06:20.708 --> 06:23.750
It's not like him,
he's usually really excited

06:23.833 --> 06:26.458
to brag about
his latest adventures.

06:26.541 --> 06:29.500
Well, maybe he's just
stressed at work.

06:30.500 --> 06:31.500
Yeah.

06:38.250 --> 06:39.375
You still mad at me?

06:41.500 --> 06:43.875
(CHUCKLES) What? About what?

06:43.958 --> 06:46.208
JONATHAN: You were pretty pissed
on the phone last night.

06:48.125 --> 06:50.250
Oh, no, that was nothing. No.

06:50.333 --> 06:52.583
JONATHAN: I texted you after,
but you were probably asleep.

06:52.666 --> 06:54.125
Yeah. I was really wiped.

06:55.833 --> 06:58.666
Anyway, sorry about what I said.

06:58.750 --> 07:01.416
MIRA: Yeah, that's--
Really, please. It's nothing.

07:01.500 --> 07:03.166
Just forget it.
It's not a big deal.

07:05.041 --> 07:06.666
JONATHAN: Do you know
what I'm talking about?

07:08.208 --> 07:09.833
You mean the renovation, right?

07:09.916 --> 07:11.375
JONATHAN: Yeah. In the attic.

07:11.458 --> 07:13.250
So, anyway, I-- (SIGHS)

07:13.333 --> 07:15.208
I was just trying to say,
it was that...

07:15.291 --> 07:16.833
I get that
it's a really busy time

07:16.916 --> 07:18.583
-for you right now,
with all the acquisitions...
-Yes.

07:18.666 --> 07:21.666
...and all that, which is fine,
but the thing is that...

07:23.166 --> 07:25.125
you know, you left it mid...

07:25.208 --> 07:27.041
-MIRA: Mm-hmm.
-So when the desk's upstairs,

07:27.125 --> 07:29.791
but my books and all my papers
are downstairs,

07:29.875 --> 07:32.541
-I can't really, you know...
-I know. You're right.
You're right, you're right.

07:32.625 --> 07:34.500
-(JONATHAN CHUCKLING)
-And, as I said on the phone,

07:34.583 --> 07:38.875
um, it's your office,
so you decide what you want.

07:39.000 --> 07:41.541
Yeah. But I don't--
Mira, it was your idea,

07:41.625 --> 07:43.000
the whole renovation's
your vision.

07:43.083 --> 07:44.375
-I know. Yeah.
-It just doesn't make sense

07:44.458 --> 07:47.416
that you suddenly don't care
what part of the house is like--

07:47.500 --> 07:49.208
I'm sorry, I'm doing it again,
I'm blaming you.

07:49.291 --> 07:51.833
-It's okay, you can.
-JONATHAN: No, no, no. I...

07:51.916 --> 07:54.166
All I'm saying is that
it is fine for me

07:54.250 --> 07:56.708
to come back downstairs, okay?

07:56.791 --> 07:58.708
I will move the desk myself...

07:59.791 --> 08:01.333
and that's fine, that's it.

08:01.416 --> 08:05.375
And then you just finish it up
whenever you have the time,

08:05.458 --> 08:06.916
and that's okay.

08:07.000 --> 08:08.958
And I'm not being
passive-aggressive.

08:09.041 --> 08:11.416
I really mean it.
I'm-- I'm happy to do that.

08:12.541 --> 08:14.000
-Okay?
-Okay, fine.

08:15.583 --> 08:16.833
(CHUCKLES)

08:17.291 --> 08:18.583
Okay. Cool.

08:19.541 --> 08:22.208
Cool. Then it's settled.

08:28.083 --> 08:30.458
Oh, man, watching you eat that
is making me so hungry,

08:30.541 --> 08:33.125
I'm gonna polish off that pasta.
(SNIFFS)

08:34.458 --> 08:36.291
(FRIDGE CLATTERING)

08:39.833 --> 08:41.041
(CLEARS THROAT)

08:52.708 --> 08:53.708
What?

08:56.708 --> 08:57.750
I didn't say anything.

09:00.458 --> 09:01.541
Everything okay?

09:09.791 --> 09:11.875
Mira, what's the matter?

09:16.916 --> 09:18.000
I, um...

09:20.625 --> 09:22.541
I came back tonight
because I needed to talk to you

09:22.625 --> 09:23.708
about something.

09:25.791 --> 09:26.791
Okay.

09:27.583 --> 09:28.625
I'm here.

09:34.333 --> 09:35.708
I fell in love with someone.

09:38.500 --> 09:40.375
It sounds stupid.
It's so stupid.

09:41.541 --> 09:44.583
(SIGHS) Maybe,
maybe it's stupid. I don't know.

09:46.791 --> 09:50.083
I met him in September,
uh, in, uh, San Francisco.

09:51.666 --> 09:53.833
He's the CEO
of an Israeli startup

09:53.916 --> 09:55.875
that we're buying out.
He-- he's...

09:57.833 --> 09:59.208
Israeli, from Tel Aviv.

10:00.958 --> 10:04.666
He will be relocating out here
at some point. I mean, not...

10:04.750 --> 10:07.958
exactly here, it'll probably be
the New York office,

10:08.041 --> 10:11.083
but I don't-- I don't know
which city it's going to be,

10:11.166 --> 10:14.458
but either way, he will be...
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:15.041 --> 10:16.166
...moving to the States.

10:22.000 --> 10:24.916
He's not someone you would think
too highly of, I bet.

10:27.500 --> 10:30.625
He's not really an intellectual.
You'd probably, I don't know...

10:33.125 --> 10:35.166
make fun of him.
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

10:40.625 --> 10:43.833
I don't know how it happened,
it just-- it happened.

10:48.833 --> 10:50.375
I felt terrible about it.

10:54.750 --> 10:56.708
But it was good for me.
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:58.208 --> 11:03.375
It was-- it was really good.
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

11:05.916 --> 11:07.875
Please, say something. Please.

11:15.166 --> 11:16.375
What do you want me to say?

11:18.458 --> 11:19.625
MIRA: I know it's unforgivable

11:19.708 --> 11:21.250
that I didn't tell you
about it earlier.

11:21.333 --> 11:23.208
I mean, I just-- I couldn't.
And, um...

11:26.375 --> 11:28.000
I didn't know
what was gonna happen.

11:30.708 --> 11:32.416
I guess I thought
that you would find out

11:32.500 --> 11:34.000
on your own at some point.

11:36.291 --> 11:38.333
How was I supposed to find out?

11:41.125 --> 11:42.708
MIRA: I don't know.
You didn't...

11:42.791 --> 11:43.958
(CLEARS THROAT)

11:44.916 --> 11:47.000
Haven't...
You didn't feel anything?

11:51.833 --> 11:52.833
No.

12:00.416 --> 12:03.000
Well, that right there might be
a sign of something, I guess.

12:03.083 --> 12:04.375
Right? (CHUCKLES)

12:06.791 --> 12:08.458
-(COUGHS)
-(GLASS CLINKS)

12:08.541 --> 12:09.791
-Sorry.
-You okay?

12:09.875 --> 12:11.750
-(COUGHS)
-Here.

12:11.833 --> 12:13.166
-Here, let me...
-(SNIFFS)

12:14.416 --> 12:17.000
(WATER POURING)

12:17.916 --> 12:19.791
Here, just drink this, okay?

12:20.833 --> 12:22.000
Okay, please?

12:22.083 --> 12:24.625
So, what am I supposed to do
with this information here?

12:27.875 --> 12:29.208
I don't know. I...

12:29.291 --> 12:31.875
I thought that it would pass,
but it hasn't.

12:35.000 --> 12:36.041
(SIGHS)

12:37.250 --> 12:38.333
So it's still...

12:41.750 --> 12:42.833
it's still going on?

12:43.916 --> 12:45.083
Like, right now?

12:49.500 --> 12:50.500
Yeah.

12:55.708 --> 12:57.166
And you're gonna keep doing it?

12:59.208 --> 13:00.250
I don't know.

13:05.625 --> 13:06.625
Yes.

13:10.833 --> 13:11.833
Yeah.

13:13.666 --> 13:15.375
So why are you telling me
right now?

13:18.125 --> 13:20.208
MIRA: I don't--
I thought you should know.

13:20.291 --> 13:21.875
JONATHAN:
Why are you telling me tonight?

13:21.958 --> 13:23.458
-Why--
-I'm going to Tel Aviv,

13:23.541 --> 13:25.458
uh, with him, tomorrow night.

13:26.583 --> 13:27.875
-JONATHAN: What--
-I have to go. I have to go.

13:27.958 --> 13:30.291
Just for a little bit. I don't
know for how long, and...

13:31.458 --> 13:32.791
I'm gonna talk to Ava
in the morning,

13:32.875 --> 13:36.916
and I'm gonna tell her that,
um, I have to go away for work,

13:37.000 --> 13:38.791
which is true. I...

13:38.875 --> 13:41.000
Someone has to oversee
the transition.

13:41.083 --> 13:42.666
(SIGHS) Ackerman and I spoke,

13:42.750 --> 13:44.541
and we both agreed
that I would go-- I would do it.

13:44.625 --> 13:48.666
So I am leaving tomorrow night
at 10:00 p.m. from JFK.

13:48.750 --> 13:51.083
What do you-- why does Ackerman
need you to leave tomorrow?

13:51.166 --> 13:52.375
MIRA: No, it's not Ack--
It's not about him.

13:52.458 --> 13:53.875
It's because Poli's go--

13:56.083 --> 13:57.083
What?

14:01.958 --> 14:03.791
That's his name. It's, um...

14:06.875 --> 14:09.083
short for Poliakov,
his first name's Saul,

14:09.166 --> 14:10.708
but everyone
just calls him Poli.

14:13.708 --> 14:15.750
He's going tomorrow.
I'm gonna go with him, so...

14:16.666 --> 14:17.708
(SIGHS)

14:18.541 --> 14:19.958
You already bought a ticket?

14:22.000 --> 14:23.000
Yeah.

14:28.416 --> 14:29.500
I mean, now that I'm talking
to you,

14:29.583 --> 14:31.958
now that I'm in this house,
it's, uh...

14:35.166 --> 14:36.666
it seems crazy. (CHUCKLES)

14:40.750 --> 14:42.250
Nothing could be crazier.
It's just...

14:42.333 --> 14:44.291
it's really surreal. It's...

14:47.375 --> 14:48.750
But at least now you know.
Now you know.

14:48.833 --> 14:50.541
-That's a relief, I guess.
-I don't know anything.

14:50.625 --> 14:52.791
I don't know
what's going on here.

14:52.875 --> 14:54.916
I told you what's going on.
I don't...

14:58.916 --> 15:01.000
I don't know what else
that I can say. It's...

15:06.750 --> 15:07.750
Okay.

15:12.541 --> 15:19.041
(DISHES CLATTERING)

15:21.041 --> 15:22.166
Go ahead, I'll be right up.

15:40.958 --> 15:42.791
(PHONE CHIMES)

15:59.041 --> 16:05.916
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:31.000 --> 16:36.541
♪ (TUNE PLAYING ON IPAD) ♪

16:58.000 --> 16:59.500
JONATHAN: You have marks
on your back.

16:59.583 --> 17:00.583
What?

17:01.916 --> 17:02.916
Sorry.

17:10.625 --> 17:13.416
MIRA: Uh, I need
some things for the...

17:13.500 --> 17:15.666
Did you have a chance
to pick up the dry cleaning?

17:18.708 --> 17:21.291
-No, no, I didn't.
-MIRA: That's okay.

17:21.375 --> 17:23.583
You can pick it up yourself
in the morning.

17:23.666 --> 17:25.083
Yeah. I'm not sure
I'll have time.

17:25.166 --> 17:27.583
I wanna be with Ava until
I drop her off at preschool,

17:27.666 --> 17:29.458
and then I have to run
to a meeting,

17:29.541 --> 17:30.625
but it's okay. Never mind.

17:34.166 --> 17:35.625
How long are you going for?

17:36.666 --> 17:39.250
MIRA: I don't know. It depends.

17:39.333 --> 17:42.875
JONATHAN: On-- on what?
Is it something that you're...

17:42.958 --> 17:44.750
-still trying to figure out?
-Three months.

17:53.208 --> 17:54.416
JONATHAN: I see.

18:00.416 --> 18:01.458
Okay.

18:03.666 --> 18:04.708
And, uh...

18:06.333 --> 18:08.666
What about Ava?
Have you thought about...

18:08.750 --> 18:10.166
I'll see her
every other weekend.

18:10.250 --> 18:11.791
-Got it in the contract.
-JONATHAN: You will?

18:11.875 --> 18:14.458
It'll be a long weekend,
Friday to Sunday, so...

18:14.541 --> 18:16.000
Flight's 11 hours,
not the end of the world.

18:16.083 --> 18:19.000
I'll get a hotel nearby
and she can stay with me.

18:19.083 --> 18:21.458
And then there's Skype
and there's FaceTime,

18:21.541 --> 18:23.416
I mean, we--
I could talk to her every night.

18:23.500 --> 18:24.583
It's a seven-hour
time difference,

18:24.666 --> 18:26.041
so when she gets home
from preschool,

18:26.125 --> 18:27.083
I'll be home from work.

18:27.166 --> 18:28.416
People do this.
I won't be the first,

18:28.500 --> 18:30.083
or the last.
Men do it all the time,

18:30.166 --> 18:31.583
and then, you know, it's not
really a big deal, so...

18:31.666 --> 18:32.916
JONATHAN: Okay. As long
as you've convinced yourself.

18:33.000 --> 18:34.291
I don't care
if I'm convincing anyone.

18:34.375 --> 18:36.291
I don't give a shit.
You can think I'm a monster,

18:36.375 --> 18:39.041
think whatever the fuck
you want, I don't care!

18:39.875 --> 18:43.166
(RAIN PATTERING)

18:50.125 --> 18:53.666
This can't-- I just--
I can't do this right now.

18:53.750 --> 18:55.500
Let's talk about this later.
I can't-- I just--

18:55.583 --> 18:56.875
-I can't do it right now.
-When's later?

18:56.958 --> 18:58.125
MIRA: When I get back.

18:58.208 --> 18:59.333
-So in four months?
-MIRA: When I get back,

18:59.416 --> 19:01.750
we will, you know,
set something up in advance

19:01.833 --> 19:03.875
with a couples therapist
or a mediator,

19:03.958 --> 19:06.875
and we'll-- we'll start
some sort of process.

19:07.833 --> 19:09.791
JONATHAN: A process of what?

19:10.541 --> 19:12.958
MIRA: Of detachment.

19:13.041 --> 19:15.125
Detachment?
What the fuck is detachment?

19:15.208 --> 19:16.291
It's a separation.

19:21.916 --> 19:23.041
You want a divorce?

19:25.833 --> 19:28.125
Maybe. I think so.

19:29.666 --> 19:32.166
But we don't have to do it
right away. I think it's best...

19:32.791 --> 19:33.750
that it's gradual,

19:33.833 --> 19:35.041
-so that Ava isn't...
-(JONATHAN SCOFFS)

19:35.125 --> 19:37.125
Yeah. Gradual, gradual.
You're leaving her overnight.

19:37.208 --> 19:38.583
-I'm not leaving her.
-JONATHAN: Really gradual.

19:38.666 --> 19:41.291
Don't say that. I'm leaving you.
I'm not leaving her.

19:41.375 --> 19:43.083
Yeah.
Try explaining that to her.

19:43.166 --> 19:44.375
MIRA: I will. I'm gonna tell her

19:44.458 --> 19:46.666
that I'll see her in less than
two weeks from today,

19:46.750 --> 19:48.958
and-- and, you know,
when I'm back from this trip,

19:49.041 --> 19:51.500
we're gonna be together a lot,
you know, all the time.

19:51.583 --> 19:52.708
(CHUCKLES) All the time.

19:57.000 --> 19:59.875
I mean, maybe the three of us
can start this process,

19:59.958 --> 20:01.375
you know, over Skype
with a family counselor--

20:01.458 --> 20:03.666
I'm not really interested in
going along with your process.

20:04.250 --> 20:05.250
MIRA: Okay, fine.

20:05.333 --> 20:06.875
-We won't do it.
-Good.

20:08.916 --> 20:10.916
Whatever you want.
I mean, I can't force you

20:11.000 --> 20:12.791
to do anything, so...

20:12.875 --> 20:14.833
I'm just gonna take
some clothes.

20:14.916 --> 20:16.291
That's all I need.
And of course, I'll pay

20:16.375 --> 20:19.958
for all of the help
that you need, obviously.

20:20.041 --> 20:21.625
-Okay. Thank you.
-MIRA: You don't need to worry

20:21.708 --> 20:24.125
-about anything.
-Sounds great.

20:26.041 --> 20:27.958
MIRA: When I get back,
we can talk about the rest,

20:28.041 --> 20:30.458
but I'm sure we'll work it out.

20:30.541 --> 20:33.000
I don't wanna fight you,
Jonathan. I just wanna leave.

20:33.083 --> 20:35.125
Okay. Well, you know what,
if it's really that urgent,

20:35.208 --> 20:37.125
why don't you just leave
right now? Go ahead.

20:37.208 --> 20:39.291
Leave if it's so urgent for you,
just-- you can leave right now.

20:39.375 --> 20:41.541
Urgent? Do you know how long
I've wanted to leave?

20:41.625 --> 20:43.166
JONATHAN: I'm not really
interested in knowing.

20:43.250 --> 20:45.958
Every day for eight months,
every morning,

20:46.041 --> 20:49.375
I've woken up with the knowledge
that I cannot be here anymore.

20:49.458 --> 20:50.708
That I have to go.

20:51.750 --> 20:53.666
But I didn't go. I stayed.

20:53.750 --> 20:55.291
So don't talk to me
about urgent.

20:55.375 --> 20:57.916
I fought this for months.
You were so busy

20:58.000 --> 20:59.500
with your own anger,
you didn't even notice.

20:59.583 --> 21:01.541
What? What-- what--
what did I not notice?

21:01.625 --> 21:03.125
That I was miserable.

21:04.083 --> 21:06.416
(PANTS)

21:07.583 --> 21:09.541
And we never even
talked about it.

21:13.083 --> 21:14.333
The abortion? We...

21:15.458 --> 21:17.916
we talked about it for days.
We...

21:18.875 --> 21:21.125
-It's what you wanted.
-I know.

21:21.208 --> 21:24.208
I thought that it was going
to protect what we had.

21:24.708 --> 21:25.916
It was for us.

21:28.375 --> 21:30.291
And then Kate saw
that I was in bad shape,

21:30.375 --> 21:32.166
so she took me to dinner,
she set me straight.

21:32.250 --> 21:34.375
She was like,
"Who has an abortion

21:34.458 --> 21:35.583
to save their marriage?

21:35.666 --> 21:39.166
What kind of marriage needs
an abortion to save it?"

21:46.416 --> 21:49.166
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

21:50.750 --> 21:51.916
MIRA: She's right, though.

21:54.958 --> 21:56.208
It was the other way around.

21:58.875 --> 22:01.750
I was terrified
that if I had another kid...

22:02.958 --> 22:04.625
then I could never leave.

22:08.916 --> 22:10.000
(SCOFFS)

22:11.458 --> 22:12.500
(SIGHS)

22:14.333 --> 22:16.041
Why didn't you talk to me
about it?

22:19.166 --> 22:21.583
MIRA: I couldn't.
You couldn't either.

22:22.291 --> 22:23.958
-I couldn't?
-MIRA: No.

22:24.666 --> 22:25.708
You were so angry at me,

22:25.791 --> 22:27.125
you couldn't even admit
that you were angry.

22:27.208 --> 22:29.666
How were we supposed to talk
about anything?

22:34.416 --> 22:35.416
Okay.

22:36.958 --> 22:39.083
Let's talk about it right now.

22:39.166 --> 22:41.125
-MIRA: No.
-Let's talk.

22:41.208 --> 22:43.333
-It's too late.
-JONATHAN: Come on, let's talk.

22:43.416 --> 22:45.375
Jonathan, it's too late.
It's too late.

22:45.458 --> 22:47.916
JONATHAN: Mira.
Mira, I know that I've...

22:48.000 --> 22:50.625
I've made my fair share
of mistakes, okay? And I take

22:50.708 --> 22:52.000
-responsibility for that.
-No.

22:52.083 --> 22:53.500
No. No, no, don't go there.

22:53.583 --> 22:55.041
-On this position, I--
-MIRA: You don't have
any responsibility.

22:55.125 --> 22:56.458
You didn't make any mistakes,

22:56.541 --> 22:58.750
and I didn't any mistakes,
and...

22:58.833 --> 23:01.583
(SIGHS) ...we're not gonna get
into blame because if...

23:02.875 --> 23:04.750
we do that, I will go crazy.

23:04.833 --> 23:06.791
So this isn't anyone's fault.

23:06.875 --> 23:08.625
It's just the way that it is.

23:08.708 --> 23:10.125
This is the way that it is?

23:10.208 --> 23:11.458
-What the fuck is that?
-MIRA: Yeah, it's the way
that it is.

23:11.541 --> 23:13.958
It happens to everyone.
It's so predictable,

23:14.041 --> 23:16.750
it's practically a cliché.

23:16.833 --> 23:18.583
I mean, so let's not get
into the blame game

23:18.666 --> 23:19.916
or where we went wrong
and all that,

23:20.000 --> 23:22.208
-because it's not about that.
-What is it about?

23:22.291 --> 23:24.833
I'm trying to explain to you,
but you keep trying

23:24.916 --> 23:26.791
to figure out
where you went wrong,

23:26.875 --> 23:28.916
what this has to do with you,
but it's not about you.

23:29.000 --> 23:30.125
-JONATHAN: Okay.
-It's not.

23:30.208 --> 23:32.125
Well then, tell me.
What is it? What is it about?

23:33.208 --> 23:34.500
MIRA: I don't know how.

23:36.875 --> 23:39.750
I mean, can you understand
what it means to feel like...

23:42.375 --> 23:45.625
like I'm lying here at night
and I...

23:46.416 --> 23:47.708
just feeling like I'm...

23:51.208 --> 23:53.791
I had a crazy thought
the other night where I just...

23:54.833 --> 23:56.125
I thought of checking
my own pulse

23:56.208 --> 23:57.958
to see if I was still alive.

23:58.041 --> 23:59.875
Can you understand that?

23:59.958 --> 24:04.000
Like there's no oxygen,
like you can't breathe.

24:04.083 --> 24:05.916
-Do you under--
-Yeah, yeah. That I--

24:06.000 --> 24:07.750
-That I can understand.
-Yeah, well, yeah.

24:07.833 --> 24:12.625
Of course you can. So imagine
like a constant asthma attack.

24:13.375 --> 24:14.416
Entire days...

24:15.250 --> 24:16.666
where you just feel...

24:17.875 --> 24:19.500
suffocated,

24:19.583 --> 24:22.125
and the whole time,
I'm just thinking...

24:24.416 --> 24:25.916
"Is this it?" It's like...

24:27.416 --> 24:30.208
Is this all I'm gonna have?
Just like...

24:33.000 --> 24:34.083
this?

24:37.333 --> 24:38.375
Without any...

24:39.333 --> 24:40.375
feeling?

24:41.791 --> 24:42.791
Without feeling?

24:46.000 --> 24:47.833
When you're in this house,
you don't--

24:47.916 --> 24:49.125
-No.
-You don't feel anything?

24:49.208 --> 24:50.416
That's not what I meant.

24:51.583 --> 24:53.625
I love Ava so much, and I...

24:57.625 --> 24:58.750
I love you.

25:01.750 --> 25:03.750
I didn't even know
what the problem was

25:03.833 --> 25:06.083
until this happened, and...

25:06.166 --> 25:08.583
then I remembered what
it was like, and now I...

25:08.666 --> 25:09.833
I can't go back.

25:11.458 --> 25:13.791
You can go back.
You can,

25:13.875 --> 25:16.291
-you just don't want to.
-No, I can't.

25:16.375 --> 25:18.000
I can't.
I tried a hundred times.

25:18.625 --> 25:20.375
Believe me, I tried.

25:20.458 --> 25:22.875
Over and over. I can't do it.

25:26.083 --> 25:28.375
I know you think I'm spoiled
and I'm pathetic.

25:28.458 --> 25:30.541
Look, I don't think that.
I don't know why you--

25:30.625 --> 25:31.833
Well, maybe I do.

25:32.791 --> 25:34.000
(SIGHS)

25:36.791 --> 25:39.416
I thought I was better than this
but I guess I'm not.

25:39.500 --> 25:41.375
Mira, please, this is bullshit
and you know it.

25:41.458 --> 25:43.500
-No, I don't.
-(SIGHS)

25:47.208 --> 25:48.875
I mean, you've known me forever.

25:51.333 --> 25:53.583
How long did you think
that we could just, like...

25:55.291 --> 25:56.708
go on like this? Just...

25:57.708 --> 25:59.541
living without any...

26:03.041 --> 26:04.541
JONATHAN: What? Without what?

26:06.791 --> 26:07.958
I don't know, just...

26:11.333 --> 26:13.416
-Passion.
-JONATHAN: Uh-huh.

26:14.875 --> 26:16.291
-I hate that word. It's--
-Right.

26:16.375 --> 26:18.250
It's-- it's really--
it's embarrassing,

26:18.333 --> 26:20.125
it sounds pathetic,
but, you know...

26:22.541 --> 26:23.875
that's, uh...

26:32.541 --> 26:34.875
-Who is he?
-(EXHALES)

26:36.416 --> 26:37.416
What?

26:38.458 --> 26:39.500
JONATHAN: The guy.

26:43.166 --> 26:44.541
I wanna hear about him.

26:47.000 --> 26:48.416
Why? What good would that do?

26:50.125 --> 26:51.166
I wanna know.

26:51.250 --> 26:52.791
Why? Why do you wanna
torture yourself?

26:52.875 --> 26:55.458
Do you have a picture of him?
Of course you do.

26:57.208 --> 26:58.333
-Can I see it?
-Jonathan, no.

26:58.416 --> 26:59.625
-Please, let's not do this.
-Please?

26:59.708 --> 27:02.375
-Not right now. Don't--
-Yes, yes, right now. Right now.

27:05.041 --> 27:06.416
I'm asking to see a picture.

27:14.666 --> 27:15.666
Okay.

27:23.291 --> 27:24.333
(SNIFFLES)

27:36.250 --> 27:37.375
(JONATHAN SNIFFLES)

27:53.541 --> 27:54.583
This is recent?

27:56.041 --> 27:57.166
MIRA: About a month ago.

27:58.166 --> 27:59.208
How old is he?

28:00.291 --> 28:01.291
Twenty-nine.

28:08.166 --> 28:09.750
JONATHAN: What does he do?

28:09.833 --> 28:12.541
-I told you, he runs a startup.
-JONATHAN: Right, right, right.

28:14.791 --> 28:15.875
He's tall?

28:16.958 --> 28:18.083
MIRA: Yeah.

28:23.541 --> 28:24.625
Is he married?

28:25.416 --> 28:27.166
No. Single.

28:33.375 --> 28:34.708
(RAIN PATTERING)

28:41.541 --> 28:42.625
So, um...

28:47.458 --> 28:48.583
how'd you meet?

28:52.875 --> 28:55.916
At that party on the boat
after we...

28:56.000 --> 28:57.750
-closed the deal. Yeah.
-JONATHAN: Right, right.

28:57.833 --> 28:59.458
Yeah, yeah.
I remember that party.

29:01.666 --> 29:04.208
So, how did it happen?

29:11.458 --> 29:12.583
What do you wanna know?

29:13.416 --> 29:14.458
JONATHAN: How it happened.

29:20.583 --> 29:22.500
He walked up to me and...

29:22.583 --> 29:24.958
he told me that he liked
the way that I was dancing.

29:26.208 --> 29:27.500
JONATHAN:
Since when do you dance?

29:30.416 --> 29:31.666
I haven't in a long time.

29:34.083 --> 29:35.375
But there was, uh...

29:36.875 --> 29:38.333
I'd had a lot to drink,
and there--

29:38.416 --> 29:40.375
and there was
a lot of coke there. So, yeah.

29:40.458 --> 29:43.625
(INHALES)
I was dancing and, um,

29:45.375 --> 29:46.458
he came over.

29:47.375 --> 29:49.250
Mm-hmm. And?

29:50.541 --> 29:51.583
And...

29:53.666 --> 29:55.708
he said that I was the first...

29:57.791 --> 29:59.208
American woman he had met

29:59.291 --> 30:01.208
who wasn't constantly trying
to please everyone,

30:01.291 --> 30:02.666
who didn't need to be liked.

30:05.375 --> 30:06.458
JONATHAN: Hmm.

30:08.125 --> 30:10.416
MIRA: And then we talked
until 2:00 in the morning.

30:13.458 --> 30:14.666
And then what?

30:19.333 --> 30:20.458
And...

30:22.958 --> 30:24.083
then we kissed.

30:29.250 --> 30:30.458
And then, um...

30:31.375 --> 30:33.250
(SIGHS)

30:33.333 --> 30:34.583
...we went up to the room.

30:36.125 --> 30:37.541
His room?

30:37.625 --> 30:39.000
MIRA: No, my room.

30:39.083 --> 30:40.458
Your room, okay.

30:41.166 --> 30:42.208
And then what?

30:44.000 --> 30:45.625
-Honey.
-JONATHAN: Just tell me.

30:59.958 --> 31:01.541
It was mostly funny at first.

31:01.625 --> 31:03.166
-It was funny?
-MIRA: Yeah.

31:04.500 --> 31:07.833
Um, I was just--
I was laughing hysterically.

31:07.916 --> 31:11.333
It was really awkward,
and... (SIGHS)

31:17.833 --> 31:19.416
But it was also liberating...

31:20.500 --> 31:21.666
to laugh like that.

31:26.333 --> 31:27.416
JONATHAN: Mm-hmm.

31:30.250 --> 31:32.416
MIRA: And then we didn't leave
the room for two days.

31:33.375 --> 31:35.500
I told, uh, everyone I was sick.

31:35.583 --> 31:36.833
I-- I told you that too.

31:40.333 --> 31:41.750
And then I came back and I...

31:43.916 --> 31:47.000
prayed that you couldn't see it
on me, but you were...

31:47.083 --> 31:50.250
you were just so happy
to see me happy again,

31:52.166 --> 31:53.500
and calm, and...

31:56.333 --> 31:58.666
We started having sex again too.

32:02.958 --> 32:03.958
Yeah.

32:07.000 --> 32:09.583
-JONATHAN: Does he know that?
-No.

32:16.125 --> 32:20.500
Every day, I told myself
it had to stop, every day.

32:22.500 --> 32:24.291
I couldn't do it.

32:24.375 --> 32:27.958
(SNIFFLES) And I even told him,
I told him I wanted out, but...

32:30.041 --> 32:31.583
I couldn't go through with it.

32:31.666 --> 32:33.458
He wouldn't let me go.
(SNIFFLES)

32:37.166 --> 32:38.458
-JONATHAN: You can still end it.
-Uh-uh.

32:38.541 --> 32:40.125
-JONATHAN:
You just don't want to, Mira.
-I can't.

32:40.208 --> 32:42.708
-JONATHAN: You can.
-I can't. I'm in love with him.

32:42.791 --> 32:44.958
-You're in love with him.
You're in love with him.
-MIRA: I'm happy with him.

32:45.041 --> 32:47.583
-Yeah. I'm in love with him.
-Okay.

32:47.666 --> 32:48.958
And he's good for me.

32:52.083 --> 32:54.083
I am-- I'm happy again.

32:54.166 --> 32:55.416
You've seen that. I mean,

32:55.500 --> 32:57.166
even people at the office
have said

32:57.250 --> 32:59.750
that I'm finally
like myself again.

32:59.833 --> 33:01.333
I'm so vibrant, and...

33:02.958 --> 33:04.833
even Ava. I'm--

33:04.916 --> 33:07.458
I mean, you saw
how we got-- we got so close,

33:07.541 --> 33:09.166
and it's like suddenly I--

33:09.250 --> 33:11.875
I had so much patience for her.

33:14.208 --> 33:16.458
I'm not-- Honey, I'm not
saying this to try to hurt you.

33:16.541 --> 33:19.791
I'm just trying to explain,
like, why I can't give it up.

33:19.875 --> 33:21.291
If I-- I'm gonna go
out of my mind

33:21.375 --> 33:23.083
-if I don't leave right now.
-Right now?

33:23.166 --> 33:24.458
-Like, right this second?
-MIRA: Yeah.

33:24.541 --> 33:27.375
If I don't leave right now,
I know I'm never going to.

33:27.458 --> 33:28.916
(BREATHING SHAKILY) So...

33:30.666 --> 33:33.250
I just-- I wish you could like
listen to yourself for a second

33:33.333 --> 33:35.833
'cause if you could,
you'd think you're nuts.

33:35.916 --> 33:37.541
No, don't patronize me.
-It's crazy.

33:37.625 --> 33:39.666
I'm not trying to patronize you,
I'm not.

33:39.750 --> 33:41.291
I'm just telling you
that this is not you.

33:41.375 --> 33:42.500
-MIRA: It is me.
-You don't talk like this.

33:42.583 --> 33:43.791
-It's absolutely me.
-JONATHAN: It's not you.

33:43.875 --> 33:46.000
You're not this person.
You don't do shit like this.

33:46.083 --> 33:47.125
Just without thinking.

33:47.208 --> 33:48.458
It's insanity,
what you're doing.

33:48.541 --> 33:50.541
-It's not insanity. It's me.
-It's gonna leave you--

33:50.625 --> 33:53.375
It's me! If you think it isn't,
you haven't been listening
to me all this time.

33:53.458 --> 33:55.416
I'm listening. I'm listening,
and I'm trying to understand.

33:55.500 --> 33:57.041
-I'm trying. Believe me.
I'm trying to understand, okay?
-MIRA: No, you understand.

33:57.125 --> 33:58.583
You understand. You're just
trying to convince me to stay,

33:58.666 --> 34:01.291
-and I don't wanna be convinced.
-All I'm asking for you

34:01.375 --> 34:03.125
-is to postpone the trip...
-No.

34:03.208 --> 34:04.541
-...for a few weeks.
-I can't.

34:04.625 --> 34:06.958
Just-- Yes, you can, you can.
It's more than reasonable

34:07.041 --> 34:09.333
for me to ask you to do that.

34:09.416 --> 34:12.416
If it's really meant to be
with this guy,

34:12.500 --> 34:14.791
a few weeks is not gonna
make any difference.

34:18.125 --> 34:21.666
You need to think
about Ava for a second,

34:22.708 --> 34:23.833
if not about me.

34:25.958 --> 34:27.750
-Don't say that. Please don't.
-JONATHAN: What?

34:27.833 --> 34:30.875
What exactly do you think
is gonna happen here

34:32.500 --> 34:35.666
every day and every night
while you're gone?

34:35.750 --> 34:37.250
Have you thought about that?

34:39.708 --> 34:42.750
-Will you think about that?
-MIRA: I think that you...

34:44.083 --> 34:48.000
are the best dad in the world,
and I think that I'm...

34:55.083 --> 34:57.041
(SOBS) I just...

34:57.125 --> 34:58.333
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

34:58.416 --> 35:01.166
It's gonna be the best
for her too.

35:01.250 --> 35:03.958
JONATHAN: How could you--
how could you possibly say that?

35:09.208 --> 35:11.625
MIRA: (SOBS) Because it's true.

35:19.958 --> 35:25.791
(CRYING)

35:44.875 --> 35:46.291
(CRYING CONTINUES)

36:07.125 --> 36:08.333
JONATHAN: Sweetie.

36:09.333 --> 36:10.416
(MIRA SNIFFLES)

36:13.000 --> 36:14.000
JONATHAN: Honey.

36:19.208 --> 36:20.625
We can survive this.

36:23.833 --> 36:25.916
We can get through it.

36:26.000 --> 36:28.583
We can talk. We know
how to talk to each other.

36:28.666 --> 36:30.458
MIRA: You'll never forgive me.

36:30.958 --> 36:32.166
(SNIFFLES)

36:33.500 --> 36:34.958
I think I can.

36:37.791 --> 36:38.958
We can...

36:39.583 --> 36:41.458
I think we can...

36:41.541 --> 36:43.666
we can get through it together.
We can...

36:47.666 --> 36:49.041
go to therapy. We'll, you know,

36:49.125 --> 36:51.458
maybe it'll bring us
closer together.

36:53.541 --> 36:54.625
(SNIFFLES)

36:54.708 --> 36:58.083
JONATHAN: We have something
so real between us,

36:58.166 --> 36:59.666
something so big.

37:01.041 --> 37:02.583
You've been so good
for me, honey,

37:02.666 --> 37:04.083
and I know that I've been good
for you.

37:04.166 --> 37:05.625
-I know I have.
-You have.

37:07.625 --> 37:09.958
Then let's not just blow it
all up in an instant.

37:10.041 --> 37:11.875
Okay? Just think about that.

37:13.333 --> 37:15.416
-It won't work.
-JONATHAN: Why? Why--

37:15.500 --> 37:17.083
