51:57.208 --> 51:59.333
JONATHAN: Mira, will you
just sit down for a second?

51:59.416 --> 52:01.708
You know, I'm gonna pick--
pick her up today after school.

52:01.791 --> 52:04.333
Um, yeah, I'll have time
before the flight.

52:04.416 --> 52:06.041
I could-- I'll take her
to Vaniglia,

52:06.125 --> 52:08.291
maybe I'll talk to her there,
and then you could meet us

52:08.375 --> 52:09.583
-to take her home.
-JONATHAN: Veronica's already

52:09.666 --> 52:10.875
planning to pick her up
from school today.

52:10.958 --> 52:12.416
It's okay, I'll call her.
I'll tell her everything

52:12.500 --> 52:13.833
-so that way you don't have to--
-Where are you going?

52:13.916 --> 52:15.708
-It's 7:00 in the morning.
-MIRA: Uh, to the office.

52:15.791 --> 52:17.458
I called a car.

52:17.541 --> 52:19.791
It's-- The office
is still closed.

52:19.875 --> 52:20.875
MIRA: Well, I've got a key.

52:20.958 --> 52:22.791
Will you please just listen
for a second?

52:22.875 --> 52:24.541
(SIGHS) What?

52:24.625 --> 52:27.166
JONATHAN: This is, uh,
it's just surreal.

52:27.250 --> 52:29.375
-It's delusional.
-Yeah, I know.

52:29.458 --> 52:31.291
Then, no. No, I don't accept it.

52:31.375 --> 52:32.958
We're gonna sit here
and we're gonna talk

52:33.041 --> 52:34.625
as long as it takes, okay?

52:34.708 --> 52:37.541
-MIRA: We talked last night.
-No. No, we yelled at each other

52:37.625 --> 52:39.666
for an hour, that was--
that's not the same thing.

52:39.750 --> 52:41.458
MIRA: It's not gonna do
any good. I mean--

52:41.541 --> 52:43.333
It's not gonna do any--
What is this? What is this thing

52:43.416 --> 52:45.166
-where we can't talk
to each other, Mira?
-(PHONE BUZZES)

52:45.250 --> 52:46.666
I want to talk to you, and

52:46.750 --> 52:48.500
-you don't want to talk to me.
-No, you don't want to talk
to me.

52:48.583 --> 52:50.041
-What kind of cruelty is that?
-You want to keep me here
at all costs.

52:50.125 --> 52:52.416
I want to talk to you.
I want to...

52:52.500 --> 52:55.083
I want to sit here 'till there's
smoke coming out of our ears

52:55.166 --> 52:57.916
and we've--
we've gone through all of--

52:58.000 --> 53:00.291
all of the angles and figure out
where we went wrong

53:00.375 --> 53:01.791
and how we can fix it.

53:02.916 --> 53:04.333
I'm not attracted
to you anymore.

53:04.416 --> 53:05.500
How do you fix that?

53:25.000 --> 53:26.125
(JONATHAN SIGHS)

53:30.208 --> 53:31.208
Mira.

53:33.041 --> 53:35.958
Jonathan, please,
let me go, please.

53:43.791 --> 53:45.541
(CRIES) Please.

53:52.750 --> 53:54.000
(MIRA SNIFFLES)

53:57.458 --> 54:00.208
(SOBS) Let me go.

54:05.791 --> 54:07.791
(CRYING)

54:09.500 --> 54:10.583
Let me go.

54:11.833 --> 54:12.958
Jonathan.

54:17.916 --> 54:19.416
(BOTH SOB)

54:21.583 --> 54:23.500
MIRA: I'll text you
when I'm with Ava.

54:23.583 --> 54:26.166
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

54:26.250 --> 54:28.583
-(LUGGAGE CLATTERING)
-(JONATHAN SOBS)

54:37.208 --> 54:38.250
Ready to go?

55:07.708 --> 55:09.500
Let me get that for you.

55:42.000 --> 55:45.250
